-- AT&T expands board to 14, appoints Glenn Hutchins as member
-- By Marina Lopes in Washington
-- Mon Jun 30, 2014 11:45AM EDT
-- None



June 30 (Reuters) - AT&T Inc <T.N> will expand its board of directors to 14 members from 13 and has appointed Glenn Hutchins, a member of the Federal Reserve Bank of New York's board of directors, to fill the new vacancy, the company said on Monday.

